Commit: b4e0b8d4d0634e79f8c4dcf8cfa434db3a97f0be&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="169515" author="adilger" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2016 18:45:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, it should be fine to remove this exclusion.  This problem was a result of lnet-selftest consuming all network bandwidth and causing the MDS nodes to go into recovery.  This was later fixed to stop all Lustre services when running lnet-selftest and there shouldn&apos;t be any problem to re-enable it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
